<l>meṉpulattu vayaluḻavar</l>
<l>vaṉpulattup pakaṭuviṭṭuk</l>
<l>kuṟumuyaliṉ kuḻaiccūṭṭoṭu</l>
<l>neṭuvāḷaip palluviyaṟ</l>
<l>paḻañcōṟṟup pukavaruntip</l>
<l>putaṟṟaḷaviṉ pūccūṭi</l>
<l><gap quantity="48" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="19" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ariyalāruntu</l>
<l>maṉaikkōḻip paimpayiriṉē</l>
<l>kāṉakkōḻik kavarkuraloṭu</l>
<l>nīrkkōḻik kūypeyarkkuntu</l>
<l>vēyaṉṉa meṉṟōḷāṉ</l>
<l>mayilaṉṉa meṉcāyalār</l>
<l>kiḷikaṭiyiṉē</l>
<l>yakalaḷḷaṟ puḷḷirīiyuntu</l>
<l>vāṅkap palanalla pulaṉaṇiyuñ</l>
<l>cīrcāṉṟa viḻucciṟappiṟ</l>
<l>ciṟukaṇ yāṉaip peṟalarun tittaṉ</l>
<l>cellā nallicai yuṟantaik kuṇātu</l>
<l>neṭuṅkai vēṇmā ṉaruṅkaṭip piṭavū</l>
<l>raṟappeyarc cāttaṉ kiḷaiyēm peruma</l>
<l>muṉṉā ṇaṇpakaṟ curaṉuḻantu varuntik</l>
<l>katirnaṉi ce<gap quantity="35" reason="lost" unit="character"/> mālait</l>
<l>taṉkaṭait tōṉṟi yeṉṉuṟa vicaittaliṟ</l>
<l>ṟīṅkural <gap quantity="20" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ki ṉarikuraṟ ṟaṭāriyō</l>
<l>ṭāṅkuniṉṟa veṟkaṇṭu</l>
<l>ciṟitunillāṉ perituṅkūṟā</l>
<l>ṉaruṅkalam varavē yaruḷiṉaṉ vēṇṭi</l>
<l><gap quantity="8" reason="lost" unit="character"/>yeṉa vuraittaṉṟi nalkit taṉmaṉaip</l>
<l>poṉpōṉ maṭantaiyaik kāṭṭi yivaṉai</l>
<l>yeṉpōṟ pōṟṟeṉ ṟōṉē yataṉkoṇ</l>
<l>ṭavaṉmaṟava lēṉē piṟaruḷḷa lēṉē</l>
<l>yakaṉñālam perituvempiṉu</l>
<l>mikavāṉu ḷeritōṉṟiṉuṅ</l>
<l>kuḷamīṉoṭun tāṭpukaiyiṉum</l>
<l>peruñcey nelliṉ kokkukir nimiral</l>
<l>pacuṅkaṭ karuṉaic cūṭṭoṭu mānti</l>
<l>viḷaivoṉṟō veḷḷaṅkoḷkeṉa</l>
<l>vuḷḷatu millatu maṟiyā</l>
<l>tāṅkamain taṉṟāl vāḻkavaṉ ṟāḷē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The ploughman of the field in the soft soil, (1)</l>
<l>letting go the bulls on the hard soil, (2)</l>
<l>eating food of old rice (5)</l>
<l>with many dishes of long Vāḷai fish (4)</l>
<l>along with a soft roast of little hare, (3)</l>
<l>wearing the flowers of golden jasmine from bushes (6)</l>
<l>………………………………. (7)</l>
<l>…………………. drinks toddy. (8)</l>
<l>Like(?) fresh crop for the house fowl (9)</l>
<l>with the seizing voice of the forest fowl (10)</l>
<l>crows the water fowl [and] makes move ???. (11)</l>
<l>??? will drive birds from the wide mire (15)</l>
<l>like parakeets [seeking] protection (14)</l>
<l>on the bamboo-like soft shoulders (12)</l>
<l>of those with soft grace who are like peacocks. (13)</l>
<l>we are kin, of great man, to Cāttaṉ with a name for virtue, (21)</l>
<l>from the heavily protected Piṭavūr of Vēṇmān with long arms(?) (20)</l>
<l>to the east of Uṟantai of unpassing fame, (19)</l>
<l>[ruled] by Tittaṉ, difficult to obtain, on a small-eyed elephant, (18)</l>
<l>of excellent glory that abounds in eminence, (17)</l>
<l>which lies close to those many good fields which are like that. (16)</l>
<l>He, seeing me who stood there, (26)</l>
<l>after having suffered enduring the desert at high noon on a former day, (22) </l>
<l>the rays much …………. evening, (23)</l>
<l>having appeared at his gate, because of the soundings of my experience, (24)</l>
<l>sweet voice ……… with [my] harsh-voiced Taṭāri drum, (25)</l>
<l>did not stand [still] a little and did not talk a lot. (27)</l>
<l>Wanting to grace [my] coming with precious ornaments, (28)</l>
<l>apart from saying ……., granting, showing [me]</l>
<l>to the gold-like girl of his house (29-30c)</l>
<l>he said ‘respect this one like me!’ Taking in that, (31)</l>
<l>I won’t forget him. I won’t think of others. (32)</l>
<l>Even though the wide world be greatly heated, (33)</l>
<l>even though flames appear much in the sky, (34)</l>
<l>even though ?????????????, (35)</l>
<l>having eaten together with green-eyed karuṉai roots (37)</l>
<l>boiled rice [as long as] crane’s nails from the paddy of the big fields, (36)</l>
<l>thinking “is there one ripening? Let the flood take [it]”, (38)</l>
<l>not knowing what is and what is not, (39)</l>
<l>it was content there, may his foot live. (40)</l>
</lg>
